{
  "name": "Guard: Steering Integrity",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Detects resurrection of deleted steering files or creation of duplicative always-loaded files.",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileCreated",
    "patterns": [
      "**/.kiro/steering/*.md"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "1. Is this file in the Deleted Files table? If yes, DELETE it immediately and warn: 'Blocked resurrection of [filename] \u2014 see steering-integrity.md for why this file was deleted.'\n2. Does this file have proper front matter with an inclusion mode? Files without front matter default to always-loaded, which burns tokens every session. If missing, flag it.\n3. If the file has inclusion: always, does its content duplicate soul.md, environment-rules.md, or any other always-loaded file? If >50% overlap, flag it and recommend merging instead.\nA new steering file was created in ~/.kiro/steering/. Read ~/.kiro/steering/context/steering-integrity.md and check:\n\n\n\n\nLog the check result to ~/shared/context/intake/organ-changes.md."
  }
}